dependencies.name: py-pip
dependencies.description: The PyPA recommended tool for installing Python packages.

dependencies.name: py-setuptools
dependencies.description:
A Python utility that aids in the process of downloading, building,
upgrading, installing, and uninstalling Python packages.

dependent_to.name: py-mmtf-python
dependent_to.description:
The macromolecular transmission format (MMTF) is a binary encoding of
biological structures.

dependent_to.name: py-msgpack-numpy
dependent_to.description:
This package provides encoding and decoding routines that enable the
serialization and deserialization of numerical and array data types
provided by numpy using the highly efficient msgpack format.
Serialization of Python's native complex data types is also supported.

dependent_to.name: py-cachecontrol
dependent_to.description:
CacheControl is a port of the caching algorithms in httplib2 for use
with requests session object.

dependent_to.name: py-zarr
dependent_to.description:
Zarr is a Python package providing an implementation of chunked,
compressed, N-dimensional arrays.

dependent_to.name: py-radical-utils
dependent_to.description:
RADICAL-Utils contains shared code and tools for various RADICAL-
Cybertools packages.

dependent_to.name: py-oslo-serialization
dependent_to.description:
The oslo.serialization library provides support for representing
objects in transmittable and storable formats, such as Base64, JSON and
MessagePack.

dependent_to.name: py-numcodecs
dependent_to.description:
Numcodecs is a Python package providing buffer compression and
transformation codecs for use in data storage and communication
applications.

dependent_to.name: miopen-tensile
dependent_to.description:
MIOpenTensile provides host-callable interfaces to Tensile library.
MIOpenTensile supports one programming model: HIP

dependent_to.name: py-pymol
dependent_to.description:
PyMOL is a Python-enhanced molecular graphics tool. It excels at 3D
visualization of proteins, small molecules, density, surfaces, and
trajectories. It also includes molecular editing, ray tracing, and
movies. Open Source PyMOL is free to everyone!

dependent_to.name: py-ray
dependent_to.description:
A system for parallel and distributed Python that unifies the ML
ecosystem.

dependent_to.name: py-python-box
dependent_to.description:
Advanced Python dictionaries with dot notation access Box will
automatically make otherwise inaccessible keys safe to access as an
attribute. You can always pass conversion_box=False to Box to disable
that behavior. Also, all new dict and lists added to a Box or BoxList
object are converted automatically.

dependent_to.name: py-datalad
dependent_to.description:
data distribution geared toward scientific datasets. DataLad makes data
management and data distribution more accessible. To do that, it stands
on the shoulders of Git and Git-annex to deliver a decentralized system
for data exchange. This includes automated ingestion of data from online
portals and exposing it in readily usable form as Git(-annex)
repositories, so-called datasets. The actual data storage and permission
management, however, remains with the original data providers.
